<!-- index.nunjucks -->
{% extends "layout.nunjucks" %}

{% block title %}
  FreshJones - Responsive Web Design
{% endblock %}

{% block header %}
  {{header.active('services')}}
{% endblock %}

{% block main %} 
  
  <section class="hero-stark">
    <div class="wrap wrap-center">
      <div class="section-summary">
        <h1 class="section-topic">Responsive Web Design</h1>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Make your site work on any device</h2>
        <p class="section-lead">Responsive websites built for all devices and orientations using industry-standard best practices</p>
        <p>
          {{ button.link('/contact.html', 'Learn More') }}
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="services-intro">
    <div class="wrap wrap-center wrap-center-narrow">
      <div class="section-spaced">
        <div class="section-summary">
          <div class="section-heading">You’ve done the hard part&hellip;</div>
          <p>Does your business rely heavily on referrals? </p>
          <p>Did you know that people are more likely to recommend and buy from businesses that have well-designed mobile websites?</p>
          <p class="bold">Its true. </p>
          <p>57% of users say they won’t recommend a business with a poorly-designed mobile website. Whether we’re at our desk, on a train, or waiting in line at the grocery store, we expect to be able to look for and find the information we want...fast and without any hassle.  And we have zero patience or tolerance for any business that isn’t able to deliver. </p>
          <p>We’ll bounce to the next site faster than a rocket full of monkeys! </p>
          <p>This couldn’t be more important for your business given that whatever we want to know, go, do, try or buy typically starts with a google search on a mobile phone or tablet. Give your business a competitive edge with responsive web design. Build a site that people find enjoyable, easy to use and one they would recommend to their friends, helping you earn more customers and grow your business.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div> 
  </section>

