    <div class="wrap wrap-center wrap-center-narrow">
      <div class="section-spaced">
        <div class="section-summary">
          <h1 class="section-heading">Anatomy of a Responsive Website</h1>
        </div>
        <div>
          <ul class="section-list section-list-bullets section-list-columns">
            <li>Works fluidly on any device</li>
            <li>Works on any orientation</li>
            <li>Fast on all devices</li>
            <li>break points based on content not on devices</li>
            <li>Optimized for readability and legibility accessibility</li>
            <li>SVG’s</li>
            <li>Easily clickable buttons</li>
            <li>Responsive images</li>
            <li>Prioritize content Consider what's most important</li>
            <li>Use screen real estate effectively</li>
            <li>Consider user interaction</li>
            <li>Design for touch and gestures</li>
            <li>Optimal reading widths</li>
            <li>Important info at the top engagement and hierarchy</li>
            <li>Change the order of content blocks on smaller screens</li>
            <li>Start with mobile first</li>
            <li>Remove modals on phones and use scroll instead</li>
            <li>Responsive videos</li>
            <li>There is no more fold - let pages scroll</li>
            <li>Focus on performance</li>
